{
  "brand": "Epson",
  "device": "PROJECTOR",
  "variant": "Epson PowerLite / EB / EMP business projectors (ESC/VP21 protocol)",
  "controlType": "RS232",
  "notes": [
    "Source: 'ESC/VP21 Command User's Guide for Business Projectors' (Epson, rev. P, Jan 2011).",
    "Wire: D-Sub 9-pin cross-over. 9600 8N1, no flow control.",
    "Format: ASCII command + CR (0x0D). Projector replies with ':' (0x3A) after executing.",
    "SOURCE codes per official manual: 10=Computer1, 20=Computer2, 30=HDMI1, A0=HDMI2, 41=Video(composite), 42=S-Video, 51=USB Display, 52=USB, 53=LAN.",
    "Note: Menu / navigation key codes (up/down/left/right/enter/menu/esc) are model-specific and not in the base ESC/VP21 reference; only 'KEY 4A' (Auto sync) is documented universally. Recommend the IR remote or HDBaseT control for menu nav.",
    "Query commands append '?' (e.g. 'PWR?', 'SOURCE?'). Responses are ASCII: 'PWR=00' (00=standby, 01=on, 02=warming, 03=cooling, 04=abnormal, 05=standby network), 'SOURCE=30' (source ID), 'LAMP=1234' (lamp hours 0-65535), 'ERR=00' (00=no error, see manual for codes), 'MUTE=ON/OFF', 'VOL=15', 'ASPECT=00' (00=Normal,10=4:3,20=16:9,30=Auto), 'LUMINANCE=00'(normal) or '01'(eco)."
  ],
